This paper introduces a new approach to neural sequence modeling, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper focuses on language modeling, sentiment classification, and character-level neural machine translation, which are all sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. 

The paper also uses convolutional layers, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the increased parallelism of the proposed approach, which is relevant to parallel computing and distributed systems, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces a new type of neural network architecture, which is relevant to artificial intelligence research, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category.
